    "<div>The proposed development, by reason of siting, scale, design and massing, would imbalance the symmetry of the terrace and would be at odds with the character of the immediate surroundings. The extensions introduce a discordance to the terrace, and introduce a mass which will be particularly prominent from the front and side elevations of the dwelling. The combined extensions would would substantially close off the openness of the corner plot at both ground and first floor levels, restricting the long term views down Woodrush Way, and would also compromise the openness of the pavement and the entrance to the cul-de-sac. The proposal is therefore contrary to:<br></div><div><br></div><div><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">-\r\nNational Planning Policy Framework </span>National Planning Policy Framework\r\n(NPPF) (December, 2023)<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">- Policy D4 of the\r\nLondon Plan (March 2021)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">- Policy\r\nCP3 of the </span>Local Development Framework (LDF) Core Strategy (July 2010)<o:p></o:p></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">-\r\nPolicies BP8 and BP11 of the </span>Local Development Framework (LDF) Borough\r\nWide Development Plan Document (DPD) (March 2011)<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">- The Residential\r\nExtensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (February 2012)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">-\r\nPolicies SP2, DMD1 and DMD6 of 